HEADWORD: Humus
<hw>Hu"mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the earth,
ground, soil.]</ety> <def>That portion of the soil formed by the
decomposition of animal or vegetable matter. It is a valuable
constituent of soils.</def> <rj><au>Graham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

